<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 07 at 4:43PM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central
Calhoun, southeastern Etowah and southwestern Cherokee Counties
through 515 PM CDT...
At 442 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hokes Bluff, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Gadsden, Jacksonville, Hokes Bluff, Glencoe, Ball Flat, Cobb City,
Knightens Crossroads and Reaves.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
